This paper discusses an alternative methodology for the analysis of algorithms, which is relevant to the field of artificial general intelligence (AGI) and automated theorem proving. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions self-improving AGI, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The concept of expected discounted reward is a common technique in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Additionally, the paper discusses algorithms that do not always terminate, which is related to the field of data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions partial algorithms for undecidable problems, which is related to the field of programming languages (cs.PL).
